<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-06T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="481" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/731a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-06T20:00:00-04:00">August 6,
                                    1943—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>396. Department’s instruction 242, July 3.<note n="19" xml:id="d481fn19">Not printed; it transmitted texts of the Soviet note of May 11,
                                    <ref target="#pg_448">p 448</ref>, and the Department’s note in
                                reply, June 15, <ref target="#pg_466">p. 466</ref>.</note> Soviet
                            note dated July 27 states that Russian Ambassador Tehran will be
                            instructed to inform Iranian Government that Soviet Government has no
                            objections to participation of American troops in control over southern
                            part of Trans-Iranian railroad. Text of note follows by air mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>